<h2>Section Numbering</h2>
<p>Use <code>data-section-numbers</code> on an <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> for &sect;-style legal/document numbering. Each <code>h2</code> gets a section number; <code>h3</code> headings get alphabetic sub-numbers.</p>
<p>This is distinct from <code>data-numbered</code> (outline-style <code>1.1</code>, <code>1.2</code> numbering).</p>

<code-block language="html" label="Section numbering">{{ sectionNumbersExample | escape }}</code-block>

<h2>Block Progress</h2>
<p>A Unicode block-character progress bar for terminal-style UI. Uses <code>role="meter"</code> for accessibility.</p>

<code-block language="html" label="Block progress">{{ blockProgressExample | escape }}</code-block>

<h2>Print URL Expansion</h2>
<p>When printing, VB automatically expands external, email, and phone link URLs after the link text so readers can see the destination. This is suppressed for image links and same-page anchors.</p>

